REFERENCE FACTS (From Nutanix 6.10 Certification Curriculum):
- CPU ready >10% = Contention (not memory issue)
- NUMA locality = Optimal at 2 vCPU per socket on 2-socket hosts
- Metro Avail Sync = Zero RPO (requires <5ms latency)
- Metro Avail NearSync = 1-15 minute RPO
- Async replication = 1hr+ RPO (snapshot schedule dependent)
- v3 API = Uses POST method for list operations
- STIG/Lockdown = Cluster security hardening via controls
- Witness VM = Prevents split-brain scenarios

