DETAILED DISAGREEMENT ANALYSIS
=====================================================================================

PART 3 DISAGREEMENTS (11 questions):

Q48 - DISAGREE (Marked: B, Mine: C)
  Marked: Prism > Replication Jobs (B) | Mine: CVM fs showrepl (C)
  Analysis: MARKED IS CORRECT. Prism Replication Jobs is the recommended first diagnostic point with clear error messages. While CVM commands are valid for deep debugging, Prism UI is primary.

Q49 - DISAGREE (Marked: D, Mine: A)  
  Marked: All tools useful; use thtool first (D) | Mine: thtool -S eth0 only (A)
  Analysis: MARKED IS CORRECT. Comprehensive CVM network analysis requires multiple tools together (ethtool, iftop, nstat), not a single tool.

Q50 - DISAGREE (Marked: A, Mine: B)
  Marked: NGT supports all Linux kernels (A) | Mine: NGT requires kernel 5.x+ (B)
  Analysis: MARKED IS CORRECT. NGT officially supports kernel 4.x and later. My assumption of 5.x minimum was incorrect.

Q51 - DISAGREE (Marked: D, Mine: C)
  Marked: All three - numactl, process affinity, Prism verification (D) | Mine: Prism NUMA only (C)
  Analysis: MARKED IS CORRECT. Complete NUMA diagnosis requires OS topology check + process affinity alignment + Prism verification together.

Q52 - DISAGREE (Marked: D, Mine: A)
  Marked: Insufficient bandwidth OR remote capacity (D) | Mine: Bandwidth only (A)
  Analysis: MARKED IS CORRECT. Slow seeding can result from either cause; both must be investigated.

Q53 - DISAGREE (Marked: C, Mine: B)
  Marked: Daily for 90 days minimum (C) | Mine: Daily+weekly+monthly tiered (B)
  Analysis: MARKED IS CORRECT. Both approaches meet 90-day compliance, but C specifies the minimum requirement directly. B is more storage-efficient but is an optimization, not the baseline requirement.

Q55 - DISAGREE (Marked: C, Mine: B)
  Marked: 50ms depends on interval; 50ms in 1s = 5% ready (C) | Mine: 50ms is negligible (B)
  Analysis: MARKED IS CORRECT. CPU ready time is a PERCENTAGE metric, not absolute milliseconds. Interpretation requires knowing the measurement interval. This is a critical distinction.

Q57 - DISAGREE (Marked: D, Mine: C)
  Marked: All three required - Windows Features, Registry, Permissions (D) | Mine: Permissions only (C)
  Analysis: MARKED IS CORRECT. SMB Previous Versions requires: 1) Windows Feature enabled, 2) Registry keys set, 3) Share restore permissions. All three are mandatory.

Q58 - DISAGREE (Marked: D, Mine: B)
  Marked: Depends on NIC bonding configuration (D) | Mine: Auto-failover to remaining uplinks (B)
  Analysis: MARKED IS CORRECT. Failover behavior (Active-Backup vs. Balance-ALB vs. LACP) depends entirely on host OS NIC bonding mode. Nutanix doesn't mandate a specific mode. I incorrectly assumed universal automatic failover.

Q59 - DISAGREE (Marked: D, Mine: A)
  Marked: Reduce to 6 vCPU with 30-50% headroom (D) | Mine: Keep 8 vCPU, add RAM (A)
  Analysis: MARKED IS CORRECT. Right-sizing formula: (Peak 45% of 8 cores) + headroom = 5-6 cores target. Over-provisioning at 8 vCPU wastes resources; 6 vCPU provides appropriate headroom.

Q60 - DISAGREE (Marked: B, Mine: C)
  Marked: CVM disk I/O processing via iostat (B) | Mine: Hypervisor cache (C)
  Analysis: MARKED IS CORRECT. High latency with acceptable IOPS indicates I/O path bottleneck, not cache. Check CVM processing first via iostat.

